WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:14.305
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

3
00:00:14.389 --> 00:00:15.682
I checked everywhere.

4
00:00:15.765 --> 00:00:17.851
but no CCTV cameras
cover the rooftop at all.

5
00:00:17.934 --> 00:00:21.438
But one from the next-door building
might capture a small part of it.

6
00:00:21.521 --> 00:00:23.523
Can you explain and show me?

7
00:00:23.606 --> 00:00:24.524
Of course.

8
00:00:24.607 --> 00:00:26.234
The quality is terrible though.

9
00:00:26.317 --> 00:00:28.570
-You can barely make anything out.
-Okay.

10
00:00:28.653 --> 00:00:30.071
-Let's see.
-Yes. sir.

11
00:00:32.615 --> 00:00:33.575
This is it.

12
00:00:34.075 --> 00:00:36.119
-Can you zoom in?
-Yes.

13
00:00:46.504 --> 00:00:48.048
What if someone was here?

14
00:00:49.966 --> 00:00:52.135
What if someone pushed him off?

15
00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:20.288
What brings you here?

16
00:01:20.955 --> 00:01:22.415
Isn't it chaotic at the ERPB?

17
00:01:22.499 --> 00:01:25.126
It's more chaotic in my mind.

18
00:01:27.128 --> 00:01:29.756
I'm wondering
why you came back to this school.

19
00:01:29.839 --> 00:01:31.966
reported bullying as soon as you arrived.

20
00:01:32.050 --> 00:01:34.677
and are doing this now.

21
00:01:39.182 --> 00:01:40.433
Have you done your homework?

22
00:01:44.604 --> 00:01:45.438
Oh. sorry.

23
00:01:46.022 --> 00:01:47.398
I sounded like a salesperson.

24
00:01:48.191 --> 00:01:49.984
If you know what's going on.

25
00:01:50.485 --> 00:01:51.694
I can tell you everything.

26
00:01:52.737 --> 00:01:55.198
I know you want the ERPB gone.

27
00:01:55.281 --> 00:01:56.533
And why would that be?

28
00:02:02.122 --> 00:02:03.498
Probably because of this.

29
00:02:07.168 --> 00:02:09.712
Heart Pills most recently.
Butterfly Pills two years ago.

30
00:02:10.880 --> 00:02:11.965
What are they now?

31
00:02:12.048 --> 00:02:13.591
Diamond.

32
00:02:15.260 --> 00:02:16.886
I guess you don't have any proof.

33
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:19.681
Otherwise. you'd have called the police
or arrested me.

34
00:02:19.764 --> 00:02:21.975
But here you are. chatting away with me.

35
00:02:24.602 --> 00:02:27.021
You and Ms. Choi

36
00:02:27.522 --> 00:02:29.566
were made for each other.

37
00:02:30.066 --> 00:02:32.986
You're so alike. sticking your nose
in other people's business.

38
00:02:33.069 --> 00:02:35.572
I wonder if you'll share the same fate.

39
00:02:48.334 --> 00:02:49.335
Hey.

40
00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:52.213
Why are you here?
I said I'm not coming to school.

41
00:02:52.297 --> 00:02:53.381
You punk.

42
00:02:53.464 --> 00:02:56.593
Did you expect me to just say.
"Okay. sure. take care"?

43
00:02:56.676 --> 00:02:58.178
That wouldn't do.

44
00:02:58.261 --> 00:03:00.180
Hey. wait. Come here.

45
00:03:00.847 --> 00:03:03.683
Every time you skip school.
you're injured like this.

46
00:03:03.766 --> 00:03:06.227
Oh. that looks pretty bad.

47
00:03:06.311 --> 00:03:08.146
-Let me put some cream on it.
-I'm fine.

48
00:03:08.229 --> 00:03:09.647
Just stay still.

49
00:03:12.275 --> 00:03:13.276
Let's see this side.

50
00:03:14.027 --> 00:03:16.738
I don't know what you've been up to.

51
00:03:16.821 --> 00:03:18.740
but do it at school.

52
00:03:18.823 --> 00:03:20.408
It's the safest place. okay?

53
00:03:20.909 --> 00:03:22.785
The safest place? Since when?

54
00:03:22.869 --> 00:03:24.537
It's not just me.

55
00:03:24.621 --> 00:03:26.873
Lots of teachers
are trying to make it safe.

56
00:03:26.956 --> 00:03:29.542
We'll make school a safe place. I promise.

57
00:03:30.460 --> 00:03:32.003
Here. promise.

58
00:03:34.047 --> 00:03:35.548
That's how you break a finger.

59
00:03:37.675 --> 00:03:38.801
You little punk.

60
00:03:39.385 --> 00:03:41.221
Fine. don't come. I won't either.

61
00:03:41.304 --> 00:03:43.973
I'll follow you around forever.
You think I'm bluffing?

62
00:03:44.057 --> 00:03:46.059
You know what my boyfriend calls me?

63
00:03:46.142 --> 00:03:49.312
Flypaper.
Once I catch you. I never let go.

64
00:03:49.395 --> 00:03:52.357
I'm coming to pick you up
tomorrow morning. Got it?

65
00:04:06.120 --> 00:04:08.831
Hey. Gyu-cheol. Good morning.

66
00:04:08.915 --> 00:04:11.417
Hey. come on. Breakfast…

67
00:04:11.501 --> 00:04:12.794
Gyu-cheol.

68
00:04:14.504 --> 00:04:16.506
Wait. Oh. come on.

69
00:04:16.589 --> 00:04:17.757
-Cho Gyu-cheol.
-Yes?

70
00:04:17.840 --> 00:04:19.342
I'm his homeroom teacher.

71
00:04:19.425 --> 00:04:20.969
You're students. right?

72
00:04:21.052 --> 00:04:22.387
-Put that out.
-Fucking hell.

73
00:04:23.846 --> 00:04:24.973
Gyu-cheol. come on.

74
00:04:25.056 --> 00:04:26.015
-Let's go.
-See you.

75
00:04:26.099 --> 00:04:27.517
-Don't look.
-We'll call you.

76
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:44.826
Hey. what the hell are you thinking?

77
00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:48.496
The Samgeori guys who came at you
are now after your ass.

78
00:04:48.579 --> 00:04:50.623
Are you seeing that bitch. Choi Ga-yun?

79
00:04:52.709 --> 00:04:55.253
Do you know what Ms. Choi made me realize?

80
00:04:56.629 --> 00:04:59.340
The school is full of people.

81
00:04:59.424 --> 00:05:01.259
So? What about it?

82
00:05:01.342 --> 00:05:03.886
Imagine they were all customers.

83
00:05:03.970 --> 00:05:04.929
-Get inside.
-Nice.

84
00:05:05.013 --> 00:05:09.225
It'd be easy to dodge the cops
and move the product back and forth.

85
00:05:09.934 --> 00:05:11.519
Best of all.

86
00:05:11.602 --> 00:05:14.981
we'd get hundreds of new customers
every year.

87
00:05:22.989 --> 00:05:23.906
Oh man. it's cold.

88
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:24.824
Ms. Choi.

89
00:05:29.245 --> 00:05:30.163
Gyu-cheol.

90
00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:31.706
You're in uniform.

91
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:35.001
I figured I'd come to school properly now.

92
00:05:35.084 --> 00:05:36.919
Hey. that's a great decision.

93
00:05:37.003 --> 00:05:39.130
That's a good boy.

94
00:05:40.715 --> 00:05:43.343
I won't touch your hair
since you have your own style.

95
00:05:43.426 --> 00:05:46.346
You haven't eaten. have you?
Want to grab some <i>gimbap</i>?

96
00:06:15.750 --> 00:06:17.668
I BELIEVE IN YOU. GYU-CHEOL!

97
00:06:34.727 --> 00:06:36.938
If she'd just turned a blind eye
back then.

98
00:06:37.021 --> 00:06:39.482
you two would be married by now.

99
00:06:39.565 --> 00:06:40.400
Right?

100
00:06:47.115 --> 00:06:49.826
What's that for?
 You're not gonna hit me. are you?

101
00:06:54.705 --> 00:06:56.082
You shouldn't do that.

102
00:06:56.666 --> 00:06:58.960
There's already a stir
about excessive punishment.

103
00:06:59.043 --> 00:07:01.379
If you hit me now.

104
00:07:01.462 --> 00:07:03.131
it'd be a real personal vendetta.

105
00:07:06.426 --> 00:07:08.136
So don't make a move.

106
00:07:08.219 --> 00:07:11.431
If you don't do anything.
nothing will happen--

107
00:07:19.730 --> 00:07:20.898
I'm sorry. Inspector.

108
00:07:21.566 --> 00:07:22.692
I was wrong.

109
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:24.777
I'm really sorry.

110
00:07:24.861 --> 00:07:27.155
I'm really sorry. Inspector.
Please spare me.

111
00:07:27.238 --> 00:07:29.073
I'm sorry.

112
00:07:30.283 --> 00:07:31.367
I was wrong.

113
00:07:31.868 --> 00:07:33.453
Please spare me just this once.

114
00:07:33.536 --> 00:07:35.455
Please. I'm sorry!

115
00:07:35.538 --> 00:07:37.373
TEACH YOU A LESSON

116
00:07:38.332 --> 00:07:39.750
<i>I'm really sorry.</i>

117
00:07:39.834 --> 00:07:42.753
<i>I'm really sorry. Inspector.</i>
<i>Please spare me.</i>

118
00:07:43.379 --> 00:07:45.339
This is exactly
what I was concerned about.

119
00:07:45.423 --> 00:07:46.716
Only a few days ago.

120
00:07:46.799 --> 00:07:49.427
excessive punishment
drove Lee Chi-ho to attempt suicide.

121
00:07:49.510 --> 00:07:52.388
Now. Cho Gyu-cheol. doing well at school.
has been assaulted.

122
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:54.140
Why do you think this happened?

123
00:07:54.223 --> 00:07:55.975
The ERPB went to Jinwon High.

124
00:07:56.058 --> 00:07:58.478
<i>targeting Cho Gyu-cheol from the start.</i>

125
00:07:59.479 --> 00:08:01.481
<i>They went there for personal revenge.</i>

126
00:08:01.564 --> 00:08:04.484
<i>looking for an excuse to harass him.</i>

127
00:08:05.193 --> 00:08:06.277
<i>In the end.</i>

128
00:08:06.986 --> 00:08:09.906
<i>it was Lee Chi-ho who was sacrificed.</i>

129
00:08:10.656 --> 00:08:12.658
I won't stand by and allow such cruelty.

130
00:08:13.242 --> 00:08:18.247
I will see to it that the ERPB.
fueled by personal revenge. is dismantled.

131
00:08:19.790 --> 00:08:21.751
<i>With opinion polls</i>

132
00:08:21.834 --> 00:08:26.464
<i>showing that more than 50% of the public</i>
<i>support disbanding the ERPB.</i>

133
00:08:26.547 --> 00:08:29.050
<i>the president</i>
<i>is under considerable pressure</i>

134
00:08:29.133 --> 00:08:31.469
<i>during the lame-duck period of his term.</i>

135
00:08:31.969 --> 00:08:34.972
<i>Despite strong resistance</i>
<i>from the opposition party.</i>

136
00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:37.642
<i>the president</i>
<i>has so far kept the ERPB in place.</i>

137
00:08:37.725 --> 00:08:39.644
<i>-But his approval rating is at 20%.</i>
-Hello?

138
00:08:39.727 --> 00:08:42.438
<i>To navigate this</i>
<i>and bring his term to a steady close…</i>

139
00:08:42.522 --> 00:08:44.315
I'll come see you now.

140
00:08:46.567 --> 00:08:47.985
It's the ERPB!

141
00:08:56.452 --> 00:08:58.204
What are you doing here?

142
00:08:58.287 --> 00:09:00.331
The ERPB shouldn't come
to schools anymore.

143
00:09:00.414 --> 00:09:04.168
{\an8}We're neither potential criminals
nor targets of personal revenge.

144
00:09:04.252 --> 00:09:06.379
I'm here to investigate Lee Chi-ho's case.

145
00:09:06.462 --> 00:09:09.173
Why would the ERPB investigate

146
00:09:09.257 --> 00:09:11.717
when they caused
Chi-ho to end up like that?

147
00:09:11.801 --> 00:09:15.221
Do you really think
you can conduct a fair investigation?

148
00:09:25.898 --> 00:09:27.858
<i>The ERPB's duties will be suspended</i>

149
00:09:27.942 --> 00:09:32.071
<i>until the investigation</i>
<i>into the student's suicide attempt</i>

150
00:09:32.154 --> 00:09:34.031
at Jinwon High School

151
00:09:34.949 --> 00:09:36.117
is concluded.

152
00:09:37.618 --> 00:09:38.578
Accordingly.

153
00:09:38.661 --> 00:09:41.122
<i>the duties of the ERPB inspectors</i>

154
00:09:41.831 --> 00:09:42.748
<i>will be suspended.</i>

155
00:09:51.090 --> 00:09:53.593
DEPUTY DIRECTOR BONG GEUN-DAE
ERPB

156
00:10:34.800 --> 00:10:36.052
Hey.

157
00:10:36.927 --> 00:10:39.221
Everything is set.
When do we start selling?

158
00:10:39.305 --> 00:10:41.807
Now that the ERPB's out of the way.
we can get started.

159
00:10:42.642 --> 00:10:44.935
First. send samples
to each school's main dealer.

160
00:10:46.604 --> 00:10:48.356
Have them drum up business with those.

161
00:10:48.439 --> 00:10:51.651
Tell them
once a school hits over 100 customers.

162
00:10:51.734 --> 00:10:54.445
we'll start the drop for real.

163
00:10:54.528 --> 00:10:57.281
We'll need a shitload of runners.
Just us isn't enough.

164
00:10:58.699 --> 00:11:01.452
Schools aren't just full of customers.

165
00:11:01.535 --> 00:11:03.204
They've got runners too.

166
00:11:03.287 --> 00:11:05.164
And they're all minors.

167
00:11:05.665 --> 00:11:07.792
No one suspects students.

168
00:11:08.292 --> 00:11:11.212
And even if they get caught.
they'll get out right away.

169
00:11:11.712 --> 00:11:13.214
Best of all.

170
00:11:13.714 --> 00:11:15.341
they're disposable.

171
00:11:24.350 --> 00:11:27.353
I flip sneakers with this guy
for some pocket money.

172
00:11:28.020 --> 00:11:29.730
But there are so many scams

173
00:11:29.814 --> 00:11:32.650
that people want to check them out
in person.

174
00:11:34.568 --> 00:11:36.654
All you have to do is deliver them.

175
00:11:39.824 --> 00:11:40.658
Okay.

176
00:11:46.664 --> 00:11:47.832
Hey.

177
00:11:47.915 --> 00:11:49.834
Oh. hello.

178
00:11:51.460 --> 00:11:53.838
{\an8}SOYEON GIRLS' HIGH SCHOOL

179
00:11:53.921 --> 00:11:55.131
They're the right ones.

180
00:12:02.179 --> 00:12:03.389
Yeah. it checks out.

181
00:12:04.348 --> 00:12:05.182
Here.

182
00:12:05.891 --> 00:12:07.810
How was it? Easy. right?

183
00:12:07.893 --> 00:12:08.811
Wanna do it again?

184
00:12:09.770 --> 00:12:10.813
Can I?

185
00:12:10.896 --> 00:12:13.149
If you do. that would be great.

186
00:12:20.072 --> 00:12:22.074
-Hello.
-You're here.

187
00:12:22.158 --> 00:12:23.117
-Gyu-cheol.
-Hey.

188
00:12:23.200 --> 00:12:24.201
You're here.

189
00:12:24.285 --> 00:12:25.786
Go on.

190
00:12:35.004 --> 00:12:36.797
Thanks. Can't wait to wear them.

191
00:12:51.061 --> 00:12:53.314
It's called biodiversity.

192
00:12:53.397 --> 00:12:56.025
There's genetic diversity.
species diversity.

193
00:12:56.108 --> 00:12:57.610
ecosystem diversity…

194
00:12:58.360 --> 00:13:01.030
Jin-hyeok and Ju-won. focus.

195
00:13:01.113 --> 00:13:05.367
Traits within the same species
are determined by genetic information.

196
00:13:05.451 --> 00:13:09.371
So what do we call the part of DNA
that stores this information?

197
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.207
We call it genes.

198
00:13:12.124 --> 00:13:15.169
We're in the middle of class.
What's with everyone today?

199
00:13:15.669 --> 00:13:17.046
Let's all focus.

200
00:13:19.632 --> 00:13:20.925
-Looks good.
-Right?

201
00:13:21.008 --> 00:13:23.219
Hey. is this art class or what?

202
00:13:23.302 --> 00:13:25.262
You're going all out with the brushes.

203
00:13:26.013 --> 00:13:27.598
You don't need this. do you?

204
00:13:27.681 --> 00:13:29.475
You're so pretty with a petite face.

205
00:13:29.558 --> 00:13:30.768
So jealous.

206
00:13:30.851 --> 00:13:33.479
Thanks. but I used to have a big face

207
00:13:34.063 --> 00:13:35.231
like you two.

208
00:13:35.314 --> 00:13:38.275
-Sorry. I actually just lost some weight.
-Really?

209
00:13:39.151 --> 00:13:40.569
What kind of diet was it?

210
00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:42.196
I took pills.

211
00:13:43.823 --> 00:13:45.407
They're hard to get.

212
00:13:46.075 --> 00:13:47.952
Try them. and if they work. let me know.

213
00:13:48.035 --> 00:13:49.662
-Thanks.
-You sure I can have these?

214
00:13:49.745 --> 00:13:51.413
-Yeah.
-This is crazy.

215
00:13:51.497 --> 00:13:52.998
<i>Pitch done.</i>

216
00:13:53.082 --> 00:13:55.334
<i>I need more samples. Please send them.</i>

217
00:13:56.460 --> 00:13:57.294
Oh. ma'am. I--

218
00:13:57.378 --> 00:13:59.839
Oh. Seong-gu.
Seong-jun was in a motorcycle accident.

219
00:13:59.922 --> 00:14:02.883
I have to go to the hospital.
so tell the class to self-study.

220
00:14:05.177 --> 00:14:09.014
Seong-jun got badly hurt
in a motorcycle accident.

221
00:14:09.098 --> 00:14:11.016
Our teacher's gone to the hospital.

222
00:14:12.935 --> 00:14:14.311
Holy shit!

223
00:14:14.395 --> 00:14:17.356
Seong-jun's been delivering like crazy
and actually bought a bike.

224
00:14:17.439 --> 00:14:19.358
Fuck. really? Let me see.

225
00:14:20.693 --> 00:14:22.444
-Let me see.
-What is it? Show me too.

226
00:14:22.528 --> 00:14:23.863
-Get lost.
-Hey. wait.

227
00:14:23.946 --> 00:14:26.198
-I'm a fucking genius.
-Why?

228
00:14:26.282 --> 00:14:28.951
We can just take over
that punk Seong-jun's routes. Right?

229
00:14:29.034 --> 00:14:30.119
Right?

230
00:14:32.288 --> 00:14:33.581
-True.
-We're pros.

231
00:14:33.664 --> 00:14:35.875
<i>Doesn't it feel off in school lately?</i>

232
00:14:35.958 --> 00:14:39.587
More kids are absent or leaving early.
and everyone seems kind of distracted.

233
00:14:39.670 --> 00:14:41.422
I'm so scared of kids these days.

234
00:14:41.505 --> 00:14:42.965
When the ERPB was around.

235
00:14:43.048 --> 00:14:46.343
I didn't exactly feel respected.
but I did feel protected.

236
00:14:46.427 --> 00:14:48.929
It feels like we're back
to how things used to be.

237
00:14:57.563 --> 00:14:58.981
LOOKING FOR ADHD MEDS
OK. CAN DO

238
00:15:01.483 --> 00:15:02.401
NEED BEAUTY PILLS

239
00:15:02.484 --> 00:15:04.320
Wow. fucking hell.

240
00:15:05.738 --> 00:15:10.117
We have about 17 schools in Seoul alone.
with roughly 100 orders from each.

241
00:15:10.200 --> 00:15:12.369
Looks like
all that sample-pushing paid off.

242
00:15:17.416 --> 00:15:19.168
Let's start selling for real today.

243
00:15:19.251 --> 00:15:21.921
Then should I blast it out
on Telegram right now?

244
00:15:23.464 --> 00:15:24.840
{\an8}CHO GYU-CHEOL
DROP IT ONCE PAID

245
00:15:27.468 --> 00:15:28.469
DROP IT ONCE PAID

246
00:15:28.552 --> 00:15:29.637
DROP IT ONCE PAID

247
00:15:45.986 --> 00:15:47.821
Can I go to the nurse's office?

248
00:15:49.031 --> 00:15:51.450
Ma'am. I've got a terrible headache too.

249
00:15:51.533 --> 00:15:55.120
Ma'am. I'm really sorry.
but my stomach hurts so much. Excuse me.

250
00:15:57.456 --> 00:15:58.582
Ma'am.

251
00:15:59.166 --> 00:16:03.671
Well. my grandma is really sick.
so I've got to rush home now.

252
00:16:04.171 --> 00:16:05.422
I'll see you tomorrow.

253
00:16:07.383 --> 00:16:08.384
Damn it.

254
